s:2;text-align:left}</style></head><body class="c34 doc-content"><p class="c39 title" id="h.fctkd9l160z7"><span>Game Design Document (GDD)</span></p><p class="c0 c4"><span class="c7"></span></p><p class="c29 subtitle" id="h.vngj0ddqo2dq"><span class="c25">Die Tryin&rsquo;</span></p><p class="c0 c4"><span class="c7"></span></p><p class="c14"><span class="c3"><a class="c2" href="#h.orjphw9foo5j">1. Introduction&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;2</a></span></p><p class="c8"><span class="c7"><a class="c2" href="#h.qkjo1wye2f7y">1.1. Scope of the document&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;2</a></span></p><p class="c8"><span class="c7"><a class="c2" href="#h.agpucdberhxb">1.2. Elevator pitch&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;2</a></span></p><p class="c14"><span class="c3"><a class="c2" href="#h.dkwebavy3ce">2. Game Overview&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;2</a></span></p><p class="c8"><span class="c7"><a class="c2" href="#h.6an3rbmlxrow">2.1. Game concept&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;2</a></span></p><p class="c8"><span class="c7"><a class="c2" href="#h.wkp9bunr3dvr">2.2. Audience&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;2</a></span></p><p class="c8"><span class="c7"><a class="c2" href="#h.e1383bjfc05z">2.3. Genre&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;2</a></span></p><p class="c8"><span class="c7"><a class="c2" href="#h.wozggf5e2tgd">2.4. Setting&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;3</a></span></p><p class="c8"><span class="c7"><a class="c2" href="#h.2d0g43qomr1h">2.5. Player&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;3</a></span></p><p class="c8"><span class="c7"><a class="c2" href="#h.86gcu1fxftyz">2.6. Core loop&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;3</a></span></p><p class="c8"><span class="c7"><a class="c2" href="#h.4dsgsqs8nnjg">2.7. Look &amp; Feel&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;4</a></span></p><p class="c14"><span class="c3"><a class="c2" href="#h.m7ronjwofttr">3. Gameplay&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;4</a></span></p><p class="c8"><span class="c7"><a class="c2" href="#h.lwjj4rwtxzqu">3.1. Objectives&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;4</a></span></p><p class="c8"><span class="c7"><a class="c2" href="#h.3w9ccow83ivt">3.2. Play flow&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;4</a></span></p><p class="c14"><span class="c3"><a class="c2" href="#h.9j0d9v6zcl2">4. Mechanics&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;4</a></span></p><p class="c8"><span class="c7"><a class="c2" href="#h.iun9evf3d82h">4.1. Rules&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;4</a></span></p><p class="c8"><span class="c7"><a class="c2" href="#h.pkfphbxfezsp">4.2. Economy&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;4</a></span></p><p class="c8"><span class="c7"><a class="c2" href="#h.f6yfihxkqrke">4.3. Player interaction&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;6</a></span></p><p class="c8"><span class="c7"><a class="c2" href="#h.3adx767bv6ye">4.4. Assets&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;6</a></span></p><p class="c14"><span class="c3"><a class="c2" href="#h.lbaxwgq732o5">5. Graphics and audio&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;6</a></span></p><p class="c8"><span class="c7"><a class="c2" href="#h.h9q1yxrzhyyq">5.1. Visual system&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;6</a></span></p><p class="c14 c21"><span class="c7"><a class="c2" href="#h.4bv6v7k3rxb8">5.1.1. Player camera&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;6</a></span></p><p class="c8"><span class="c7"><a class="c2" href="#h.54bpfjn2f06d">5.2. Interface&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;6</a></span></p><p class="c0 c4"><span class="c7"></span></p><p class="c0 c4 c21"><span class="c7"></span></p><p class="c0 c4 c21"><span class="c7"></span></p><p class="c0 c4"><span class="c7"></span></p><p class="c0 c4"><span class="c7"></span></p><p class="c0 c4"><span class="c7"></span></p><p class="c0 c4"><span class="c7"></span></p><p class="c0 c4"><span class="c7"></span></p><p class="c0 c4"><span class="c7"></span></p><p class="c0 c4"><span class="c7"></span></p><h2 class="c24 c35" id="h.n2vohzvkh3vk"><span class="c13"></span></h2><h2 class="c24 c35" id="h.y4q8jn2lep62"><span class="c13"></span></h2><h2 class="c24 c35" id="h.wg4m8tiy8ezn"><span class="c13"></span></h2><h2 class="c24 c35" id="h.3dx52oc4zc2p"><span class="c13"></span></h2><p class="c0 c4"><span class="c7"></span></p><h2 class="c24" id="h.orjphw9foo5j"><span class="c13">1. Introduction</span></h2><h3 class="c1" id="h.qkjo1wye2f7y"><span class="c15">1.1. Scope of the document</span></h3><p class="c0"><span class="c7">This document is for </span></p><h3 class="c1" id="h.agpucdberhxb"><span class="c15">1.2. Elevator pitch</span></h3><p class="c0"><span class="c7">Die Trying is a fast-paced, highly strategic, card game where the goal is to accumulate the </span></p><p class="c0"><span class="c7">most wealth before you kick the bucket. It&rsquo;s a PvP class based game where you get to choose between a knight, mage, or thief and have to decide when to use your abilities to gain the upper hand against your competitors. The winner is whoever makes the most money, not the last man standing.</span></p><h2 class="c24" id="h.dkwebavy3ce"><span class="c13">2. Game Overview</span></h2><h3 class="c1" id="h.6an3rbmlxrow"><span>2.1. Game concept</span></h3><p class="c0"><span class="c7">Card drawing game where each draw is filled with tension, will you gain more gold or draw a trap and take damage. Surviving longer means you will have more opportunities to make money, but while the deck shrinks, it becomes more likely for you to draw a trap. The deck is primarily filled with gold and traps, with some potions and treasures along the way.</span></p><h3 class="c1" id="h.wkp9bunr3dvr"><span>2.2. Audience</span></h3><p class="c0"><span>Die Trying is designed for people between their early teens to early 40s. It&rsquo;s designed to be casual and quick, making it fun for new players and more competitive for tabletop gamers. Decisionmaking is key as there are only a few major decisions to be made. The games last about 10 minutes</span></p><h3 class="c1" id="h.e1383bjfc05z"><span class="c15">2.3. Genre</span></h3><p class="c0"><span>Card game / Strategy with survival elements</span></p><h3 class="c1" id="h.wozggf5e2tgd"><span class="c15">2.4. Setting</span></h3><p class="c0"><span class="c7">The setting is a fantasy world where mages, dungeons, and potions appear. The world is meant to be loose and comedic to contribute to its fast paced nature.</span></p><p class="c0 c4"><span class="c7"></span></p><h3 class="c1" id="h.2d0g43qomr1h"><span class="c15">2.5. Player</span></h3><p class="c0"><span class="c7">3 or more players. Each play as either mage, knight or thief and have different resources allocated to them through gameplay. The knight has shields, mage has mana, and the thief has dodging abilities. Each class is played differently, but is kept simple enough to pick up quickly.</span></p><p class="c0 c4"><span class="c7"></span></p><table class="c33"><tr class="c9"><td class="c5" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c0"><span class="c3">Class</span></p></td><td class="c20" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c0"><span class="c3">HP</span></p></td><td class="c11" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c0"><span class="c3">Role</span></p></td><td class="c26" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c0"><span class="c3">Strength</span></p></td><td class="c22" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c0"><span class="c3">Weakness</span></p></td><td class="c32" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c0"><span class="c3">Passive</span></p></td><td class="c16" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c0"><span class="c3">Abilities</span></p></td></tr><tr class="c27"><td class="c5" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c0"><span class="c3">Knight</span></p></td><td class="c20" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c0"><span class="c3">10</span></p></td><td class="c11" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c0"><span class="c3">Tank</span></p></td><td class="c26" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c0"><span class="c3">Physical traps</span></p></td><td class="c22" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c0"><span class="c3">Spell Traps</span></p></td><td class="c32" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c0 c4"><span class="c7"></span></p></td><td class="c16" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c0"><span class="c3">50% phys dmg reduction</span></p><p class="c0"><span class="c3">Block: negate all dmg from one trap (uses armor charge)</span></p><p class="c0"><span class="c3">Repair: restore armor. 1st: 4g, +1g each time</span></p></td></tr><tr class="c27"><td class="c5" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c0"><span class="c3">Mage</span></p></td><td class="c20" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c0"><span class="c3">10</span></p></td><td class="c11" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c0"><span class="c3">Controller</span></p></td><td class="c26" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c0"><span class="c3">Debuffs (half effect)</span></p></td><td class="c22" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c0"><span class="c3">Physical traps</span></p></td><td class="c32" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c0 c4"><span class="c3"></span></p></td><td class="c16" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c0"><span class="c3">Gain 1 mana/turn (max 5)</span></p><p class="c0"><span class="c3">Foresee (1 mana): peek next 3 cards</span></p><p class="c0"><span class="c3">Swap (3 mana): move top card anywhere in deck</span></p><p class="c0"><span class="c3">Gilded (2 mana): double one gold card&#39;s value</span></p></td></tr><tr class="c27"><td class="c5" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c0"><span class="c3">Thief</span></p></td><td class="c20" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c0"><span class="c3">10</span></p></td><td class="c11" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c0"><span class="c3">Opportunist</span></p></td><td class="c26" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c0"><span class="c3">Trap dodging</span></p></td><td class="c22" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c0"><span class="c3">Both</span></p></td><td class="c32" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c0"><span class="c37">Vanish: roll d6 on trap draw, dodge on 4+</span></p></td><td class="c16" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c0"><span class="c3">Dead Man&#39;s Cut: steal 15% of any player&#39;s gold on their death</span></p><p class="c0 c4"><span class="c3"></span></p></td></tr></table><p class="c0 c4"><span class="c7"></span></p><h3 class="c1" id="h.86gcu1fxftyz"><span>2.6. </span><span>Core loop</span></h3><p class="c0"><span class="c7">There are the class cards that determine what each player is. This stays in their hand for the whole time. The turns follow this sequence:</span></p><ol class="c36 lst-kix_z1kieggrfbk6-0 start" start="1"><li class="c0 c19 li-bullet-0"><span class="c7">Player can use their class related abilities</span></li><li class="c0 c19 li-bullet-0"><span class="c7">Player can play any other potion or treasure card from their hand</span></li><li class="c0 c19 li-bullet-0"><span class="c7">Players draw a card from the shared deck.</span></li></ol><ol class="c36 lst-kix_z1kieggrfbk6-1 start" start="1"><li class="c0 c28 li-bullet-0"><span class="c7">If it&rsquo;s a trap, the player must reveal the trap card and the effects are activated unless the player has an ability that blocks it</span></li><li class="c0 c28 li-bullet-0"><span class="c7">If it is any other card, the player does not reveal it and adds it to their hand</span></li></ol><ol class="c36 lst-kix_z1kieggrfbk6-0" start="4"><li class="c0 c19 li-bullet-0"><span class="c7">Next player starts their turn</span></li></ol><h3 class="c1" id="h.4dsgsqs8nnjg"><span>2.7. Look &amp; Feel</span></h3><p class="c0"><span class="c7">Comedic cartoon aesthetic. The tone is a parody of fantasy games and the art in the cards exemplifies this. The game is supposed to be chaotic and fast. The feel of the game is exaggerated and supposed to be funny.</span></p><h2 class="c24" id="h.m7ronjwofttr"><span class="c13">3. Gameplay</span></h2><h3 class="c1" id="h.lwjj4rwtxzqu"><span class="c15">3.1. Objectives</span></h3><p class="c0"><span>The main objective for &nbsp;players is to have the most amount of gold left when the game ends. To achieve this they must stay alive long enough in order to collect more gold from the deck. They have to manage their abilities and HP. They must also choose when to redirect cards and traps to others via the treasure cards.</span></p><h3 class="c1" id="h.3w9ccow83ivt"><span>3.2. Play flow</span></h3><p class="c0"><span class="c7">A typical game session lasts about 10 minutes. Players are able to accumulate resources faster in the early game, but as the traps end up getting reshuffled it becomes more likely to hit a trap in the late game. The last man standing gets a bonus of 3 gold. Because of the nature of the game, some players may die early which is why keeping the game as quick rounds means that they won&rsquo;t stay spectators for long</span></p><h2 class="c24" id="h.9j0d9v6zcl2"><span>4. Mechanics</span></h2><h3 class="c1" id="h.iun9evf3d82h"><span class="c15">4.1. Rules</span></h3><p class="c0"><span class="c7">Each player selects a class before the game starts. Class cards are then given to players and they stay in their hand.</span></p><p class="c0"><span class="c7">The deck is shuffled and then placed face down.</span></p><p class="c0"><span class="c7">Trap cards must be revealed </span></p><p class="c0"><span class="c7">A player dies when their hp reaches zero</span></p><p class="c0"><span class="c7">Gold earning is locked once the player is dead</span></p><p class="c0"><span class="c7">If there is a tie in gold, the player that survived longer wins</span></p><p class="c0 c4"><span class="c7"></span></p><h3 class="c1" id="h.pkfphbxfezsp"><span class="c15">4.2. Economy</span></h3><p class="c0"><span class="c7">The economy depends on which character you play. For the knight, repairing armor costs gold so repairing the armor is a meaningful decision that must be made. The mage uses mana so their economy relies on them surviving for long enough to build it up, finally the thief does not have an economy, instead they must outlast other players to steal from them.</span></p><p class="c0 c4"><span class="c7"></span></p><table class="c33"><tr class="c9"><td class="c10" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c0"><span class="c3">Type</span></p></td><td class="c12" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c0"><span class="c3">Card Name</span></p></td><td class="c17" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c0"><span class="c3">Count</span></p></td><td class="c6" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c0"><span class="c3">Effect / Value</span></p></td></tr><tr class="c9"><td class="c10" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c0"><span class="c3">PHYSICAL TRAP</span></p></td><td class="c12" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c0"><span class="c7">Falling Chandelier</span></p></td><td class="c17" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c0"><span class="c7">1</span></p></td><td class="c6" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c0"><span class="c7">5 dmg (Knight passive: 3 / armor: 0, Thief: dodge on d6 4+)</span></p></td></tr><tr class="c9"><td class="c10" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c0"><span class="c3">PHYSICAL TRAP</span></p></td><td class="c12" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c0"><span class="c7">Bear Trap</span></p></td><td class="c17" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c0"><span class="c7">1</span></p></td><td class="c6" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c0"><span class="c7">4 dmg (Knight passive: 2 / armor: 0, Thief: dodge on d6 4+)</span></p></td></tr><tr class="c9"><td class="c10" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c0"><span class="c3">PHYSICAL TRAP</span></p></td><td class="c12" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c0"><span class="c7">Lightning Rod</span></p></td><td class="c17" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c0"><span class="c7">1</span></p></td><td class="c6" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c0"><span class="c7">6 dmg &mdash; Knight takes +2 extra / armor still negates, Thief: dodge on 4+</span></p></td></tr><tr class="c9"><td class="c10" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c0"><span class="c3">PHYSICAL TRAP</span></p></td><td class="c12" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c0"><span class="c7">Rolling Boulder</span></p></td><td class="c17" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c0"><span class="c7">1</span></p></td><td class="c6" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c0"><span class="c7">3 dmg + 1 unblockable to LEFT player, Thief: dodge on 4+</span></p></td></tr><tr class="c9"><td class="c10" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c0"><span class="c3">DEBUFF TRAP</span></p></td><td class="c12" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c0"><span class="c7">Cursed Mushroom</span></p></td><td class="c17" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c0"><span class="c7">1</span></p></td><td class="c6" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c0"><span class="c7">Next gold card drawn is worth 2g less (Mage: 1g less)</span></p></td></tr><tr class="c9"><td class="c10" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c0"><span class="c3">DEBUFF TRAP</span></p></td><td class="c12" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c0"><span class="c7">Witch&#39;s Hex</span></p></td><td class="c17" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c0"><span class="c7">1</span></p></td><td class="c6" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c0"><span class="c7">Ability costs double for 2 turns (Mage: 1 turn)</span></p></td></tr><tr class="c9"><td class="c10" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c0"><span class="c3">DEBUFF TRAP</span></p></td><td class="c12" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c0"><span class="c7">Confusion Fog</span></p></td><td class="c17" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c0"><span class="c7">1</span></p></td><td class="c6" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c0"><span class="c7">Draw 2 cards next turn (Mage: chooses which to keep)</span></p></td></tr><tr class="c9