>6</span></p></td><td class="c6" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c0"><span class="c7">+4 HP. Use on self or gift to another player.</span></p></td></tr><tr class="c9"><td class="c10" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c0"><span class="c3">POTION</span></p></td><td class="c12" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c0"><span class="c7">Antidote</span></p></td><td class="c17" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c0"><span class="c7">4</span></p></td><td class="c6" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c0"><span class="c7">Clear all active debuffs immediately.</span></p></td></tr><tr class="c9"><td class="c10" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c0"><span class="c3">TREASURE</span></p></td><td class="c12" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c0"><span class="c7">The Great Split</span></p></td><td class="c17" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c0"><span class="c7">1</span></p></td><td class="c6" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c0"><span class="c7">All gold is revealed and split evenly. Remainder to deck.</span></p></td></tr><tr class="c9"><td class="c10" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c0"><span class="c3">TREASURE</span></p></td><td class="c12" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c0"><span class="c7">Totem of Undying</span></p></td><td class="c17" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c0"><span class="c7">1</span></p></td><td class="c6" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c0"><span class="c7">Assign to any player. On death they resurrect at half HP and stay in.</span></p></td></tr><tr class="c9"><td class="c10" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c0"><span class="c3">TREASURE</span></p></td><td class="c12" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c0"><span class="c7">Double Trouble</span></p></td><td class="c17" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c0"><span class="c7">1</span></p></td><td class="c6" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c0"><span class="c7">Choose a player. They draw 2 cards now, resolving each in order.</span></p></td></tr><tr class="c9"><td class="c10" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c0"><span class="c3">TREASURE</span></p></td><td class="c12" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c0"><span class="c7">Pass the Buck</span></p></td><td class="c17" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c0"><span class="c7">1</span></p></td><td class="c6" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c0"><span class="c7">Redirect a trap you drew to any other player. They may defend.</span></p></td></tr></table><p class="c0 c4"><span class="c7"></span></p><h3 class="c1" id="h.f6yfihxkqrke"><span class="c15">4.3. Player interaction</span></h3><p class="c0"><span class="c7">Players hit the start game, and then are shown a menu where they pick their class. From there the game begins and they can use cards in their hand, then draw, then their turn ends and the next player clicks start turn. There is a separation between the trunks so player 1 does not see what is in player 2&rsquo;s hand. The cards have onHover and onClick functions that determines what happens</span></p><p class="c0 c4"><span class="c7"></span></p><h3 class="c1" id="h.3adx767bv6ye"><span>4.4. </span><span class="c15">Assets</span></h3><p class="c0"><span class="c30">52 card deck represented by a stack</span></p><p class="c0"><span class="c30">Prefab for the cards</span></p><p class="c0"><span class="c30">Textures for the cards</span></p><p class="c0"><span class="c30">Background texture</span></p><p class="c0"><span class="c30">Dice for thief dodge</span></p><h2 class="c24" id="h.lbaxwgq732o5"><span class="c13">5. Graphics and audio</span></h2><h3 class="c1" id="h.h9q1yxrzhyyq"><span class="c15">5.1. Visual system</span></h3><p class="c0"><span class="c7">Minimalistic design for the demo. Flat background and cards as well as a stack of cards that represent the deck</span></p><h4 class="c38" id="h.4bv6v7k3rxb8"><span class="c31">5.1.1. Player camera</span></h4><p class="c0"><span class="c7">Camera switches between three points and also a start next turn screen that blocks the view for the next player</span></p><h3 class="c1" id="h.54bpfjn2f06d"><span class="c15">5.2. Interface</span></h3><p class="c0"><span class="c7">Minimal interface that counts the gold, mana, and shows your class abilities. Repair armor and use magic for knight and mage respectively.</span></p></body></html>
